title: the idea
pid: 3dea65ae-8122-49de-a69b-287992096aba
body: |2-
  When a node in the graph cites a source,
  the citation relationship should go from content to its source.
  There should be no link from 
  (the node representing) the source to the content.
  This way, from both the source and the content,
  looking backward provides an interesting answer
  to the question, 'What justifies this note's existence?'
